Name: malignant giant cell tumor of the tendon sheath
Definition: A connective tissue disease that results_in inflammation located_in synovial membrane that lines a synovial joint which causes pain and swelling.
Synonym: malignant Giant cell neoplasm of the Tendon Sheath

Name: synovial sarcoma
Definition: A synovium cancer which develops in the synovial membrane of the joints.

Name: obsolete metastatic synovial sarcoma
Definition: A synovium cancer which develops in the synovial membrane of the joints.
